Permission Boundry is attached to Role and User. As you know that policies are attached to Role/User. there might be condition when ay attached policy give too much permission you are not intent to give.
For this comses permission boundry. 
Here you can set the max permission the role/IAM can have. any permission given beyond this permission policy by any IAM or Inline policy will be null and void

Some use cases:-
  with  Resource = "muf-finance/*"    in permission boundry make sure that only resoure of finance department are accesible for that role/user
  with     Action   = ["lambda:*", "s3:*", "logs:*", "ecr:*"]    you can make sure that user/role can access only certain aws serive.
  Now even if any policy do provide the access of those resource, but permission boundry deny that.

